  "text": "The Kafka consumer group coordinator implements multiple state machines for managing different group types and member participation. The implementation spans both server-side coordinators and client-side membership managers.\n\n**Classic Group State Machine (org.apache.kafka.coordinator.group.classic):**\n\nThe ClassicGroupState enum (group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/classic/ClassicGroupState.java) defines five states with specific valid transitions:\n\n- EMPTY: Initial state where the group has no members. Transitions to PREPARING_REBALANCE when members join.\n- PREPARING_REBALANCE (Join Phase): Group waits for members to join within a timeout period. Members send JoinGroup requests. Transitions to COMPLETING_REBALANCE when a leader is elected or timeout occurs.\n- COMPLETING_REBALANCE (Sync Phase): Group waits for leader to compute assignments and members to send SyncGroup requests. Transitions to STABLE when all members have synced.\n- STABLE: Active rebalance state where members can fetch and consume with current assignments. Transitions back to PREPARING_REBALANCE if a member fails, leaves, or updates metadata.\n- DEAD: Final state before cleanup. Can transition from any other state.\n\nThe ClassicGroup class (group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/classic/ClassicGroup.java) manages the group state and enforces valid transitions. ClassicGroupMember (group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/classic/ClassicGroupMember.java) tracks individual member state with awaitingJoinFuture and awaitingSyncFuture for coordination.\n\n**Modern Consumer Group State Machine (org.apache.kafka.coordinator.group.modern.consumer):**\n\nThe ConsumerGroup class (group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/modern/consumer/ConsumerGroup.java) implements an updated state machine with states:\n\n- EMPTY: No members in the group.\n- ASSIGNING: Group is computing target assignments for all members using partition assignors.\n- RECONCILING: Members are reconciling to their target assignments (pulling assignments and revoking previous partitions).\n- STABLE: All members have completed reconciliation and are in steady state.\n- DEAD: Group is marked for deletion.\n\nThe transitions flow as: EMPTY → ASSIGNING → RECONCILING → STABLE, with the ability to return to ASSIGNING from STABLE when metadata changes trigger rebalancing. ConsumerGroupMember (group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/modern/consumer/ConsumerGroupMember.java) manages member-specific state.\n\n**Share Group State Machine (org.apache.kafka.coordinator.group.modern.share):**\n\nThe ShareGroup class (group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/modern/share/ShareGroup.java) implements a simpler state machine:\n\n- EMPTY: No members.\n- STABLE: Members are actively consuming.\n- DEAD: Group being removed.\n- UNKNOWN: Initial/fallback state.\n\n**Streams Group State Machine (org.apache.kafka.coordinator.group.streams):**\n\nThe StreamsGroup class (group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/streams/StreamsGroup.java) implements:\n\n- EMPTY: No members.\n- NOT_READY: Group cannot assign tasks (topology not ready).\n- ASSIGNING: Computing task assignments.\n- RECONCILING: Members reconciling task assignments.\n- STABLE: All members have tasks assigned and reconciled.\n- DEAD: Group being removed.\n\n**State Transition Orchestration:**\n\nThe GroupMetadataManager class (group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/GroupMetadataManager.java) is the central coordinator managing all state transitions. It handles JoinGroup requests (initiating rebalance), SyncGroup requests (completing rebalance), heartbeats (maintaining stable state), and member departures (triggering new rebalance).\n\n**Client-Side State Enums:**\n\nClient-side representations are provided in:\n- clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/common/ClassicGroupState.java\n- clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/common/ConsumerGroupState.java (deprecated)\n- clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/common/GroupState.java (unified enum)\n\n**Member State Management:**\n\nThe MemberState enum (group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/modern/MemberState.java) tracks individual member reconciliation states separate from group-level states, enabling fine-grained tracking of member progress through assignment reconciliation (UNJOINED → JOINING → STABLE → RECONCILING → ACKNOWLEDGING → LEAVING → UNSUBSCRIBED).\n\nThe state machines implement the Kafka rebalancing protocol with Join (PREPARING_REBALANCE in classic, ASSIGNING in modern), Sync (COMPLETING_REBALANCE in classic, RECONCILING in modern), and Stable (STABLE across all types) phases, ensuring coordinated group membership changes and assignment distribution."
}

